<subSubSection id="079E653C5359FF99FEF380A3FC21FEB3" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F3B36B75359FF97FEF380A3FC2BF93C" blockId="7.[151,1437,1296,2043]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FEF380A3FE9CFA14" bold="true" box="[199,308,1440,1466]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks</emphasis>
. These specimens belong to the 
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FC8280A3FC6CFA14" box="[694,964,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FC8280A3FCC1FA14" authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1911" box="[694,873,1440,1466]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ooplax">Ophiura ooplax</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FD4280A3FC6CFA14" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1905" box="[886,964,1440,1466]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="trimeni">trimeni</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
group of species characterised by ovoid DAPs that rapidly become separate, three arm spines, the uppermost lengthened and thickened basally, the elongated ‘eland-horn’ shaped radial shields (
<figureCitation id="D7BF2A325359FF97FC1280EBFD28F9AC" box="[550,640,1512,1538]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[151,1436,181,1896]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. (A–B) Ophiura ljungmani, MNHN IE.2009.1623,A:dorsal and B: ventral views.(C–E) Ophiura cf. trimeni, MNHN IE.2009.1620, C: dorsal outline, D: dorsal and E: ventral views. (F–H) Ophioplinthus sp., juvenile, MNHN IE.2009.1619, F: dorsal outline, G: dorsal and H: ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404680/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
), wide oral shields with a notch at the distal end of each side, and the kite-shaped basal VAPs becoming wide and rhomboid by the 4–6th plate with a rounded distal lobe (
<figureCitation id="D7BF2A325359FF97FB01830FFA38F988" box="[1333,1424,1548,1574]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[151,1436,181,1896]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. (A–B) Ophiura ljungmani, MNHN IE.2009.1623,A:dorsal and B: ventral views.(C–E) Ophiura cf. trimeni, MNHN IE.2009.1620, C: dorsal outline, D: dorsal and E: ventral views. (F–H) Ophioplinthus sp., juvenile, MNHN IE.2009.1619, F: dorsal outline, G: dorsal and H: ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404680/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). There are some ontogenetic changes. Younger specimens have been reported to have small spines on the disc (or at least they survive collection better) (
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465359FF97FC058357FD08F9C1" author="Fell, H. B." box="[561,672,1620,1647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 37" refId="ref31002" refString="Fell, H. B. (1952) Echinoderms from Southern New Zealand. Zoological Publications of the Victoria University Wellington, 18, 1 - 37." type="journal article" year="1952">Fell 1952</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465359FF97FC988356FCDBF9C0" author="Mortensen, T." box="[684,883,1620,1647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="215 - 400" refId="ref34370" refString="Mortensen, T. (1933 a) Echinoderms of South Africa (Asteroidea: Ophiuroidea). Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening, 93, 215 - 400, pls. 8 - 19." type="journal article" year="1933">Mortensen 1933a</bibRefCitation>
), the radial shields are more rounded and distally contiguous, and the arm comb is more visible from the dorsal side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F3B36B75359FF97FEF3839FFA35F8E8" blockId="7.[151,1437,1296,2043]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
This cryptic complex has been principally recorded from around 
<collectingCountry id="379376275359FF97FD95839EFC49F919" box="[929,993,1693,1719]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FDC5839FFA8FF918" authority="H. L. Clark, 1911" authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1911" box="[1009,1319,1692,1719]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ooplax">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FDC5839FFBF7F918" box="[1009,1119,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">O. ooplax</emphasis>
H.L. 
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465359FF97FA95839FFA8FF918" author="Clark, H. L." box="[1185,1319,1692,1718]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 302" refId="ref29926" refString="Clark, H. L. (1911) North Pacific ophiurans in the collection of the United States National Museum. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 75, 1 - 302, figs. 1 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 32556" type="journal article" year="1911">Clark, 1911</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), southern 
<collectingCountry id="379376275359FF97FEA383C3FF56F974" box="[151,254,1728,1754]" name="Australia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Australia</collectingCountry>
/ 
<collectingCountry id="379376275359FF97FF3283C3FE36F974" box="[262,414,1728,1754]" name="New Zealand" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FF8483C3FCE8F975" authority="Fell, 1952" authorityName="Fell" authorityYear="1952" box="[432,832,1728,1755]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="ooplax" subSpecies="chathamensis">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FF8483C3FD6AF974" box="[432,706,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">O. ooplax chathamensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465359FF97FCFF83C3FCE8F975" author="Fell, H. B." box="[715,832,1728,1755]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 37" refId="ref31002" refString="Fell, H. B. (1952) Echinoderms from Southern New Zealand. Zoological Publications of the Victoria University Wellington, 18, 1 - 37." type="journal article" year="1952">Fell, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="379376275359FF97FDB783C3FBBBF974" box="[899,1043,1728,1754]" name="South Africa" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FA1183C3FB33F974" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1905" box="[1061,1179,1728,1754]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="trimeni">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FA1183C3FB33F974" box="[1061,1179,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">O. trimeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465359FF97FA8083C3FA30F974" author="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Smith, P. J. &amp; Mills, V. S. &amp; Smirnov, A. V. &amp; Steinke, D." box="[1204,1432,1728,1754]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="321 - 333" refId="ref35087" refString="O'Hara, T. D., Smith, P. J., Mills, V. S., Smirnov, A. V. &amp; Steinke, D. (2013) Biogeographical and phylogeographical relationships of the bathyal ophiuroid fauna of the Macquarie Ridge, Southern Ocean. Polar Biology, 36, 321 - 333. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00300 - 012 - 1261 - 9" type="journal article" year="2013">
O’Hara 
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FB2583C2FAE3F974" box="[1297,1355,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
(2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465359FF97FEA383E7FF79F950" author="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Hugall, A. F. &amp; Thuy, B. &amp; Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. V." box="[151,209,1764,1790]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="415 - 430" refId="ref34885" refString="O'Hara, T. D., Hugall, A. F., Thuy, B., Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. V. (2017) Restructuring higher taxonomy using broad-scale phylogenomics: the living Ophiuroidea. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 107, 415 - 430. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2016.12.006" type="journal article" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
) also reported specimens from tropical NW 
<collectingCountry id="379376275359FF97FC8783E7FCB2F950" box="[691,794,1764,1790]" name="Australia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Australia</collectingCountry>
that formed a distinct mitochondrial DNA clade compared to 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FE80820BFE6AF88C" authorityName="Fell" authorityYear="1952" box="[180,450,1800,1826]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="ooplax" subSpecies="chathamensis">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FE80820BFE6AF88C" box="[180,450,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">O. ooplax chathamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The only other tropical record is from off southern coast of Mindanao (
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465359FF97FAC5820BFA38F88C" author="Koehler, R." box="[1265,1424,1800,1826]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 295" refId="ref32615" refString="Koehler, R. (1930) Ophiures recueillies par le Docteur Th. Mortensen dans les Mers d'Australie et dans l'Archipel Malais. Videnskabelgie Meddelelser fra Dansk naturhistorisk Forening i Kobenhavn, 89, 1 - 295, 22 pls." type="journal article" year="1930">Koehler 1930</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, there are no known morphological characters that can reliably distinguish any of these populations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F3B36B75359FF97FEF38252FF53F855" blockId="7.[151,1437,1296,2043]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
For the present, the MD 
<specimenCount id="5982FD3E5359FF97FFEE8253FDDCF8C4" box="[474,628,1872,1899]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="generic">50 specimens</specimenCount>
are identified as 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FD0F8253FBB1F8C4" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1905" box="[827,1049,1872,1898]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="trimeni">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FD0F8253FC32F8C4" box="[827,922,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ophiura</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FDFC8252FBB1F8C4" box="[968,1049,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">trimeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They differ from typical 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FB708252FA3DF8C4" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1905" box="[1348,1429,1873,1898]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="trimeni">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FB708252FA3DF8C4" box="[1348,1429,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">trimeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FEA38277FEADF820" authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,261,1908,1934]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ooplax">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FEA38277FEADF820" box="[151,261,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">O. ooplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FF088277FDE2F820" authorityName="Fell" authorityYear="1952" box="[316,586,1908,1934]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="ooplax" subSpecies="chathamensis">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FF088277FDE2F820" box="[316,586,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">O. ooplax chathamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having shorter, wider radial shields that have a rounded rather than acute proximal angle. The MD 
<specimenCount id="5982FD3E5359FF97FF9B829BFDEFF81C" box="[431,583,1944,1971]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="generic">50 specimens</specimenCount>
were collected somewhat deeper (
<quantity id="887C9B525359FF97FDF8829BFBF4F81D" box="[972,1116,1944,1971]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2025" metricValueMax="1.685" metricValueMin="0.72" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="1202.5" valueMax="1685.0" valueMin="720.0">720–1685 m</quantity>
) than is typical for either 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FBB5829BFF40F878" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1905" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="trimeni">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FBB5829BFF40F878" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">O. trimeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345359FF97FF2682BFFE2AF878" authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1911" box="[274,386,1980,2006]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ooplax">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55359FF97FF2682BFFE2AF878" box="[274,386,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">O. ooplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are rarely found below 
<quantity id="887C9B525359FF97FCDA82BFFCEDF879" box="[750,837,1980,2007]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="1000.0">1000 m</quantity>
(although see 
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465359FF97FDC482BFFBDAF878" author="Clark, H. L." box="[1008,1138,1980,2006]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="221 - 435" refId="ref30081" refString="Clark, H. L. (1923) The echinoderm fauna of South Africa. Annals of the South African Museum, 13, 221 - 435, pls. 8 - 23." type="journal article" year="1923">Clark 1923</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465359FF97FAB482BFFA9CF878" author="McKnight, D. G." box="[1152,1332,1980,2006]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="291 - 313" refId="ref34140" refString="McKnight, D. G. (1967) Additions to the echinoderm fauna of the Chatham Rise New Zealand Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 1, 291 - 313. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00288330.1967.9515206" type="journal article" year="1967">McKnight 1967</bibRefCitation>
for deep records).
</paragraph>
<caption id="1BFB663F5356FF98FEA38283FDC4F84E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404680" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6404680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404680/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" startId="8.[151,250,1920,1944]" targetBox="[151,1436,182,1895]" targetPageId="8">
